                            <comment id="13409895" author="srowen" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 22:57:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I like it but can this be done with the existing assign() method and a DoubleFunction that adds? If not, I think a separate method like addTo() would be better than a flag.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13410427" author="ssc" created="Tue, 10 Jul 2012 16:20:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Very nice find, thank you!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I changed the code here to not use .plus() and .times(), but only .assign() on the vectors.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, I added a special handling in the assign() method for PLUS_ABS and found that two jobs in RecommenderJob need to be map-only, so I could remove the identity reducers there.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Overall this should give a huge boost to our recommenders performance!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
